          <div class="stacked" tyle="padding-bottom:15px">
            <span class="readable">&ldquo;Jefferson appeared to his enemies as an American version of Candide; Hamilton as an American Machiavelli.&rdquo;</span>
            <nobr>
              &mdash;
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/quotes/785401-jefferson-appeared-to-his-enemies-as-an-american-version-of">6 likes</a>
            </nobr>
            <div class="clear"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="stacked" tyle="padding-bottom:15px">
            <span class="readable">&ldquo;In Jefferson's mind great historical leaps forward were almost always the product of a purging, which freed societies from the accumulated debris of the past and thereby allowed the previously obstructed natural forces to flow forward into the future. Simplicity and austerity, not equality or individualism, were the messages of his inaugural march. It was a minimalist statement about a purging of excess and a recovery of essence.&rdquo;</span>
            <nobr>
              &mdash;
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/quotes/785473-in-jefferson-s-mind-great-historical-leaps-forward-were-almost-always">4 likes</a>
